The City of uMhlathuze is one of very few in the province to disinfect all taxi ranks and other public areas. RICHARDS BAY - Regular cleaning of public places is crucial in fighting the spread of the coronavirus. That’s according to the City of uMhlathuze in Richards Bay, KwaZulu-Natal north coast. The city is one of very few in the province to disinfect all taxi ranks and other public areas. READ: Home screening rolled out in KZN Richards Bay has at least two confirmed cases of COVID-19. Authorities say they’ll continue to monitor and disinfect public areas in the province’s second economic hub. Those in the taxi industry say taxi ranks and other public places are most vulnerable to spreading the coronavirus. WATCH: Taxi industry announces plans to curb COVID-19 All stakeholders agree that working together during a global crisis is key to defeating what’s been described as an invisible enemy. Authorities have vowed to deal with those breaking the national lockdown rules. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.